{"id": "1440873861905383485", "channel_id": "1385040039448412170", "type": 0, "author_id": "756552645661032682", "author_name": "enternameunavailable", "author_bot": false, "content": "I'm gonna break this down piece by piece. Because wooweee\n\nhttps://discord.com/channels/1131791637933199470/1354754985119846581/1440858438791069707\n\nStreamlining, making the server a bit more organized and better is good. Having multiple sections for channels like <#1400749543288475770> <#1433513650299076780> is good, since those channels are always active and Mori chat is a cluster mess.\n\n\nModmail... Seriously? It's ass, it's like sending a notice to city council and waiting for it to be resolved in months time. I agree reporters should be hidden to not get harassed but not mod decisions. If we're gonna use mod mail we might as well just delete this place, since it might as well be a mailbox that no one opens to read the letters.\n\nTimeout statement - these aren't a bad thing, just \"without public statement\" is literal corrupt government 101. We're just shutting protestors up for the sake of peace. Again, where do we draw the line? If your logic is sound, reasonable there is no reason why you can't say it in public chat. Please be more transparent give more orderly reasoning.\n\nThere's no reason to erase anything in server suggestions, it'll just be drowned out in endless texts and new things as time goes on and flows. This is just putting dirt and cement over an issue and saying it's done and over. Leave it so we can review it in the future. Only thing that should be removed is discussion like what Pood, lud, and pzn did last night which should have moved to gen chat.\n\nTaking it into consideration is almost meaningless, it's politician buzzwords. \n\nIf you are short-staffed please open up mod verification like some of us are asking that are more active part of the community.\n\nThe greater community as a whole I like, I spend a lot of my time in game questions, team building or lore chat. If you do want to take it to dms then do so, since it's better then getting a nothing burger <:takenotes:1357186646294138890>", "timestamp": "2025-11-20T01:18:18.820000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "agree", "emoji_id": "1400771815076528258", "count": 7}, {"emoji": "🔥", "emoji_id": null, "count": 5}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1440899856049766412", "channel_id": "1385040039448412170", "type": 0, "author_id": "1131790839291596841", "author_name": "morimensstaff01", "author_bot": false, "content": "Thank you for your trust. I need to investigate the situation before giving a response. Currently, I only have a rough idea and need more detailed information to support my judgment.\nSome players have mentioned that the administrators' handling of violations is not transparent enough. This is because we do not want negative things to further expand in the chat group, so we usually communicate privately with violators.\nWe only choose to announce very serious violations on our chat channel to remind everyone.\nBut even if it's a private message, we will still organize all the violation information to the other party, explaining what behavior they have violated and what punishment they will receive for the violation.", "timestamp": "2025-11-20T03:01:36.307000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [{"id": "1440899855819083846", "filename": "image.png", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 561444, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1385040039448412170/1440899855819083846/image.png?ex=6a3559d0&is=6a340850&hm=143b791efb25a769feaec62ec714a7f064cd69a7d60b509ff514a4367c3c0f55&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1440906322878005371", "channel_id": "1385040039448412170", "type": 0, "author_id": "1131790839291596841", "author_name": "morimensstaff01", "author_bot": false, "content": "Another situation that needs to be communicated to everyone is that although we follow community rules, the actual problems that occur are often more complex and varied. Even if we write the rules in detail, we cannot cover them. Pursuing absolute fairness and justice is almost impossible, and it is also impossible to satisfy everyone with the handling results.\nTherefore, when dealing with problems in practice, we will be more flexible and adaptable. We can only ensure that the problem is handled as fairly and justly as possible, and convincing people.\nIf you have any questions about the handling results, you can communicate with me first and I will provide a response.", "timestamp": "2025-11-20T03:27:18.119000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1440909696818085919", "channel_id": "1385040039448412170", "type": 19, "author_id": "1131790839291596841", "author_name": "morimensstaff01", "author_bot": false, "content": "<@756552645661032682>If you think the Morimens channel is chaotic, please tell me specifically what aspects are chaotic?\nIf it is a reasonable suggestion, we will consider adopting it.\nIf it's just that everyone hasn't followed the chat rules of this channel (chatting about content other than memes), (1) you can tell the other party to chat on another channel; (2) You can tell me or the administrator, and we will remind each other to turn other channels to chat (a Chinese player used to do this)\nSome people may not be very sensitive to channel classification during conversations, perhaps we can help them find the right channel to share their opinions", "timestamp": "2025-11-20T03:40:42.529000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["756552645661032682"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1440873861905383485", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1440910914709749870", "channel_id": "1385040039448412170", "type": 19, "author_id": "1131790839291596841", "author_name": "morimensstaff01", "author_bot": false, "content": "Administrators are not tyrants, we are everyone's service providers. We will not shut up a player without reason just because they say something against the administrator.🙏", "timestamp": "2025-11-20T03:45:32.897000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["964125234871545886"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1440865477818847333", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
